Class SimpleTreeNodeChangeListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.util.SimpleTreeNodeChangeListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.util.EventListener, TreeNodeChangeListener

    public class SimpleTreeNodeChangeListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeNodeChangeListener
    This very simple implementation of an TreeNodeChangeListener writes all the events to the standard out stream.

      • nodeRemoved

        public void nodeRemoved(TreeNodeRemovedEvent evt)
        Description copied from interface: TreeNodeChangeListener
        The TreeNodeRemovedEvent passed to this method provides information about the node that has been removed from a containing parent and does hence no longer belong to the SBMLDocument anymore. In addition, a pointer to its previous parent is also provided. In this way, an implementing class can identify the location within the tree where it was before.
        Specified by:
        nodeRemoved in interface TreeNodeChangeListener
        Parameters:
        evt - The event containing information about the removed TreeNode.
